Download stocks

library(tseries)
library(timeDate)
library(MASS)
library(car)
library(zoo)
## 
## Attaching package: 'zoo'
## 
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     as.Date, as.Date.numeric
library(forecast)
## This is forecast 5.8
# Load stocks
vow <- get.hist.quote(start="2006-01-01", instrument="vow.de", quote="AdjClose")
## time series starts 2006-01-02
dai <- get.hist.quote(start="2006-01-01", instrument="dai.de", quote="AdjClose")
## time series starts 2006-01-02
# Create returns
rvow <-diff(log(vow))
rdai <- diff(log(dai))

# Create list
rstocks <- list(rvow = rvow, rdai = rdai)
  • Eigenschaften der univariaten unbedingten Verteilungen
options(scipen = 10)

sapply(rstocks, function(x) c(mean=mean(x), 
                              var = var(x),
                              skew = skewness(x),
                              kurt = kurtosis(x)))
##             rvow      rdai
## mean   0.0007435 0.0004757
## var    0.0012564 0.0005204
## skew   6.4826290 0.2907375
## kurt 249.2321466 7.5207102
layout(matrix(c(1,3,2,3), 2, 2, byrow = TRUE))
sapply(rstocks, function(x) c(truehist = truehist(x),
                              qqPlot = qqPlot(x),
                              boxplot = boxplot(coredata(x))))

  • Zeitliche Abhängigkeitsstruktur der Renditen und von Transformationen der Renditen
par(mfrow = c(3, 1))
sapply(rstocks, function(x) c(ts=ts.plot(x),
                              ts_abs=ts.plot(abs(x)),
                              ts_2 = ts.plot(x^2)))

## $rvow
## NULL
## 
## $rdai
## NULL
par(mfrow = c(3, 1))
sapply(rstocks, function(x) c(acf = acf(x, na.action=na.pass),
                             acf_abs = acf(abs(x), na.action=na.pass),
                             acf_2 = acf(x^2, na.action=na.pass)))
